
# pfSense Setup Walkthrough

This is just a quick line-by-line walkthrough of how pfSense was configured for the home lab environemnt that I was setting up.

---
```
Download Link to pfSense ISO file : https://www.pfsense.org/download/

*At the time of writing this, the latest version of pfSense is 2.6.0. I selected AMD64 (64-Bit). I also selected the DVD Image (ISO) Installer and the Austin, TX USA Mirror.*
```
---

# Initial Virtual Machine Steps (VMware Workstation Pro 17)

```
1. Click on "Create a New Virutal Machine"
2. Click "Typical" for the virtual machine configuration type and then click "Next"
3. Next click "Installer Disc Image File (ISO)", then "Browse..." and select the file downloaded from the website provided above. Click "Next" to continue.
4. Rename the virtual machine and confirm the location of where the VM will be stored by clicking "Browse..." again. Click "Next" to continue.
5. 
